<HEADLINE> With BC-NJ--Black Newspapers, Adv  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated PressHere are circulation figures for a sampling of newspapers
around
the country that serve black communities:
<TEXT>
<P>
   - Atlanta Daily World: 9,000 (publishes weekly).
</P>
<P>
   - Baltimore Afro-American: 14,000 (weekly).
</P>
<P>
   - Chicago Defender: 15,000 (five days a week), down from a
weekly circulation of more than 100,000 at its peak.
</P>
<P>
   - Cleveland Call &AMP; Post: 37,580 (weekly); statewide total
including Cleveland: 71,980.
</P>
<P>
   - Louisiana Weekly: 6,500 (weekly).
</P>
<P>
   - Michigan Chronicle: 45,000 (weekly).
</P>
<P>
   - Philadelphia Tribune: 136,000 (four days a week).
</P>
<P>
   - St. Louis Sentinel: 25,000 (weekly).
</P>
<P>
   - Washington Afro-American: 15,000 (weekly).
</P>
<P>
   Source: Each newspaper's circulation department.
