   Most of the crash victims were Germans flying to New York to
join a luxury cruise through the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
   Journalists were not allowed to approach the site Saturday.
Family members were seen crying and holding red carnations after a
brief visit to the site.
</P>
<P>
   A technical investigation is being carried out by the Accident
and Inquiry Office, a part of the French Transportation Ministry.
The office is expected to release a preliminary report on the crash
on August 31.
</P>
<P>
   British Airways, the only other airliner to operate the
Concorde, suspended its flights on August 15.
</P>
