<HEADLINE> By The Associated Press  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Sunday will bring rain over most areas of upstate New
York,
possibly thunderstorms in western and central areas. Temperatures
may approach 80 in western, central, and mid-Hudson regions; cooler
weather is forecast for eastern New York and the Adirondacks.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sunday night will be partly cloudy with lows in the high 50s to
around 60.
</P>
<P>
   Monday will be partly sunny with daytime highs in the middle 70s
to low-80s, nighttime lows in the upper 50s to lower 60s.
</P>
</TEXT>
