<HEADLINE> 20 Arrested at Student Party in Va.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- A back-to-school block party just off
the James Madison University campus turned into a melee early
Saturday that was broken up by police. Twenty people were arrested.
</P>
<P>
   Police in riot gear used pepper spray and gas canisters to
disperse an unruly crowd of more than 2,000 -- mostly students --
that pelted officers with rocks and bottles.
</P>
<P>
   ''The tear gas is ridiculous. I've never seen this kind of
situation before in all my four years here, but the fact that
people are throwing bottles at the police isn't helping much
either,'' senior Scott Wilson told the school's student newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they tried to break up the party at about 11:30 p.m.
Friday after receiving complaints. One officer suffered minor
injuries, and the party was broken up by 2:30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   James Madison, a public university with an enrollment of 15,000,
is about 130 miles northwest of Richmond. Founded in 1908, it is
named for the nation's fourth president.
</P>
<P>
   Messages left for school officials Saturday were not immediately
returned.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   James Madison University: http://www.jmu.edu
</P>
</TEXT>
