<HEADLINE> French Suspect Stages Spain Escape  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADRID, Spain (AP) -- A suspected French mafioso facing murder
charges in Spain staged a spectacular escape from police custody
during a trip to a Madrid hospital, newspapers said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Michel Frigerio, a 37-year-old native of Marseille, was in the
hospital for a checkup Friday when two armed cohorts attacked his
police guards, spraying them with an aerosol irritant and beating
them with pistol butts.
</P>
<P>
   They then took off with the handcuffed Frigerio. Running through
corridors, they ran down the stairs to a side exit, where another
accomplice was waiting with a getaway car.
</P>
<P>
   The fight with police and the mad dash through the hospital
terrified patients, doctors and visitors, some of whom threw
themselves to the floor fearing a gun battle, El Pais newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
   Frigerio was awaiting trial for allegedly killing two Frenchmen
in June of last year in the southern Spanish town of Mijas. El Pais
said Frigerio is accused of shooting one of the two men 17 times.
Police say the killing was a settling of scores between rival crime
gangs.
</P>
<P>
   France has requested Frigerio's extradition because he was
sentenced in absentia to 10 years in prison in 1998, security
sources in France said. He had been convicted of drug trafficking
and criminal conspiracy.
</P>
</TEXT>
