Cooper took charge of the game in the second half. They combined for 32 of the
Comets' final 36 points. Cooper, who said she'd retire after the playoffs, hit a
3-pointer with 21 seconds to play that tied the game at 64-64 and forced
overtime. Swoopes' 31 points set a career playoff high.
AP NewsBrief by MARIA CODER 
</P>
