<HEADLINE> Three Navy members arrested for shooting pellet gun  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WILTON, N.Y. (AP) - State police Saturday charged three men
stationed at a Saratoga County Navy base with shooting a pellet gun
at cars and shooting out at least one car window.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Cecil Baird, 18; Jarod Salsman, 19; and Timothy
Berquam, 19; were shooting a pellet gun from a residence.
</P>
<P>
   All three men are from Saratoga County and are stationed at the
Kesselring Training Base in West Milton.
</P>
<P>
   They were arraigned on charges of reckless endangerment and
released to the custody of the U.S. Navy.
</P>
</TEXT>
