<BODY>
<HEADLINE> D.C. United 2, Fusion 1, OT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- D.C. United forward Raul Diaz Arce scored the
game-winning overtime goal in the 94th minute to beat the Miami
Fusion 2-1 Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Midfielder Bobby Convey sent a long pass down the center of the
field intended for Diaz Arce, but he was being shielded from the
ball by Miami defender Tyrone Marshall. However, as the ball
reached the edge of the penalty area, Marshall and Fusion
goalkeeper Nick Rimando collided, leaving the ball and Diaz Arce
untouched to score the game-winner, his fifth of the season.
</P>
<P>
   With D.C. trailing 1-0 in the 73rd minute, midfielder Nelson
Vargas failed to clear A.J. Wood's shot from just outside the
penalty area. The deflection went straight up, allowing Pete Marino
to volley his second goal of the year behind Rimando.
</P>
<P>
   Former D.C. forward Roy Lassiter needed just 37 seconds to net
the fastest goal in Miami history, gathering a deflected pass from
Martin Machon inside the six-yard penalty box to score his eighth
goal of the year. Machon has an assist in five straight games.
</P>
<P>
   With the loss, Miami (10-13-5, 35 points) trails the Columbus
Crew by three points for eighth place in MLS standings. The top
eight teams reach the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The United (7-16-6, 27 points) must win one of their final three
games to avoid finishing the season with the fewest number of wins
in an MLS season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
