<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 11 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saturday, Aug. 26, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
United, Pilots Reach Settlement
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- United Airlines and its pilots reached a tentative agreement
today in a contract dispute that forced the world's largest airline to cancel or
delay thousands of flights. The two sides met around-the-clock over the past two
days, guided by the National Mediation Board. The key issues remaining in the
talks were security and pay. A spokesman for the pilots would not provide any
details of the agreement, which he said is retroactive to April 12. The
agreement will be presented to the pilots next month.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Spanish Hikers Killed in India
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- Bandits with wooden truncheons bludgeoned and killed
a Spanish woman and her son trekking in a lower Himalayan region in northern
India and seriously wounded their British friend, officials said Saturday. The
unidentified attackers assaulted the Spaniards and threw their bodies into a
gorge Friday when they were camping in the Parvati Valley, police said. The
