in afternoon home games, losing their last nine. They haven't won a
home day game since May 14. ... Adrian Brown was 2-for-5 and now is
18-for-38 (.473) during a nine-game hitting streak. He has nine
hits in his last four games. ... Pirates 1B Kevin Young was retired
at first on an odd play in the ninth inning of Saturday's 11-4 loss
to Colorado. With runners on first and second, Young grounded to
third baseman Jeff Cirillo, who stepped on the bag to retire the
lead runner. Young beat the throw to first, then strolled off the
bag as he saw first base umpire Mike Winters throw up his hands.
Rockies 1B Todd Helton then tagged out Young, who was joined by
manager Gene Lamont in arguing that Winters called time. ... 2B
Warren Morris has played 48 games without an error since making 11
errors in his first 64 games.
Diamondbacks-Mets:
</P>
<P>
   ARIZONA: The Diamondbacks, in second place in both the NL West
and the race for the wild card, are facing an uphill club in their
attempt to return to the postseason. The Mets, the wild card
leaders, have the majors' best record since the All-Star game at
28-14. The Giants, atop the West, have the second best mark of
27-14. ... 1B Greg Colbrunn, who went 2-for-4 in Friday's 13-3 loss
at New York, improved his 2000 average against the Mets to .467
(7-for-15) and his career average against them to .332
(65-for-196). ... Randy Johnson, who didn't record a strikeout in
his 2 1-3-inning outing on Friday, had gone 351 consecutive
appearances and 342 starts since that last happened on April 15,
1989.
