<P>
   NEW YORK: Saturday marked the fourth anniversary since Bobby
Valentine took over as Mets manager, replacing the fired Dallas
Green. In that time, Valentine has 361 wins -- second best in team
history to Davey Johnson (595). ... Benny Agbayani, who reached
base in 10 straight plate appearances, flied out to center leading
of the first to end the streak. ... OF Juan LeBron was sent
outright to Class A St. Lucie and RHP Juan Aracena was sent to
Double-A Binghamton. The moves open spaces on the 40-man roster,
creating more flexibility for Sept. 1 callups. The Mets now have 37
players on the 40-man roster. General manager Steve Phillips said
he intends to promote between five and 10 players over the course
of the season's final month. ... RHPs Rick Reed and Bobby Jones,
Saturday's starter, watched the Little League World Series
championship game on television before the game, cheering on the
team from Bellaire, Texas. Bellaire lost 3-2 to Maracaibo,
Venezuela.
