<HEADLINE> Magician Upsets Moni Maker  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Magician posted a Canadian record mile 1:52.3 in
beating Moni Maker by 3&AMP;frac12; lengths Saturday in the $390,000 Maple
Leaf Trot at Woodbine Racetrack.
</P>
<P>
   The result was a disappointment for Moni Maker, harness racing's
career money leader with more than $5.2 million, who is in the
midst of a world farewell tour before becoming a broodmare.
</P>
<P>
   Lifetime Memories finished third.
</P>
<P>
   Moni Maker, with Wally Hennessey driving, took the lead at the
half-mile from Corn Cob Conch.
</P>
<P>
   But Magician, driven by Dave Miller, moved up from fifth down
the backstretch and joined Moni Maker at the front turning for home
before pulling away.
</P>
</TEXT>
